parameters:
Clea: Although Nora-san and I have different paths, fighting
for someone's sake is the same. Let's strive together.

Thief Nora: In that case, um, why don't we become
mercenaries together! With Clea-san around, we'll be as
strong as a hundred people! It'll definitely be fun!

Clea: I feel like I have things I need to do at the
Adventurer's Guild, so I'm really happy about the
invitation... but I'm sorry.

Thief Nora: That's fine! Let's both do our best! So, let's
play together, over and over again!

Noble Kasaro: Please rely on me for anything so that the
elderly man with a short remaining life, who has had his
dreams fulfilled by all of you, will have no regrets.
Clea: Please take care of my dear friend.

Captain Clevo: I will never betray my comrades again, and I
know you won't betray Nora's friends either.

Captain Clevo: More than anything, I am grateful for
introducing me to Kasaro... and for introducing me to Nora.

Thief Nora: I've returned to the Emma Mercenary Corps! From
now on, I'll do my best as a member of the mercenary corps!
Thief Nora: I'll do my best to repay you!

\CL 【Thief Nora's After Story】After becoming a mercenary
instead of a thief, Nora worked under Cleveaux and actively
engaged in tasks such as guarding nobles and merchants,
focusing mainly on the role of protecting.

\CL Although she had some attachment to her hometown, she
considered her place to be in the Emma Mercenary Corps and
passed away within the empire.

\CL Until the end, she never regained her memories or the
ability to speak the language of the beastmen.

\CL Several years after reclaiming the throne, Cleveaux
confesses his feelings to Clea, saying, Didn't we get
married!? Clea responds by accepting his proposal and
getting married.

\CL Although they couldn't have children, the entire Emma
Mercenary Corps was Nora's family.

\CL 【The Aftermath of Noble Casaro】After being offered a
position in the Senate, which she had dreamed of as a
collaborator in reclaiming the throne, she readily declined
and chose to cooperate with the Emma Mercenary Corps.

\CL Clea highly valued Cleveaux, and she instilled political
knowledge in him. Perhaps her interactions with the younger
generation paid off, as she lived a considerably long life.

\CL It was a daily routine for Cleveaux to report the growth
of the Emma Mercenary Corps to her son's grave.

Captain Cleveaux: I would like to express my gratitude to
the other two who have been truly helpful on another
occasion.

\CL 【Captain Cleveaux's After Story】As the leader of the
Emma Mercenary Corps, Cleveaux continued to learn various
things other than combat under the noble Casaro, in order to
honor the fallen comrades who had passed away.

\CL In the Third Tarasa War, she gained a reputation as the
strongest mercenary.

\CL She provided land to the relatives of the sacrificed
thief group. She successfully negotiated with Pido, a former
Senate noble who was her archenemy, and reclaimed a portion
of the land.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

You won't be able to come back, but are you really leaving
the room?
Clea (We haven't talked yet, have we?)

Thief Nora: Thank you for giving us bread back then! Clea-
san is the beginning of our story!

Thief Nora: Cool, weak, strong, and timid... I love every
single Clea-san, no matter what!
